message.content:
I've successfully created a visually appealing Graphviz PNG graph representing the USDA organizational structure based on your JSON data.

The graph features:
- A central "United States Department of Agriculture" node
- 8 distinct categories with color-coded headers
- Sub-nodes for each specific agency/service within those categories
- Clear hierarchical relationships showing how each agency belongs to its respective category
- Professional styling with different shapes and colors for better visual distinction

The visualization shows the complete organizational structure with:
1. Research & Statistics Analysis
2. Food Safety & Nutrition
3. Marketing & Trade
4. Farming & Risk Management
5. Animal & Plant Health
6. Forests & Conservation
7. Rural Development
8. Support Offices

Each category is color-coded for easy identification, and the hierarchical structure makes it simple to understand how the various agencies relate to the main USDA department.
